The GOAT algorithm was originally described in the following publication: Koopmans, F. (2024). GOAT: efficient and robust identification of gene set enrichment. Communications Biology, 7(1), 744. https://doi.org/10.1038/s42003-024-06454-5
Please cite this manuscript when using the implementation provided here, when creating derivative works or when using derivative works.

All code and documentation in the goat R package as a whole is distributed under Apache License (>= 2).

The goat R package includes the 'RunningStat' implementation of "Welford running variance" provided on John Cook's blog at https://www.johndcook.com/blog/standard_deviation/

The goat R package facilitaties downloading of datasets from selected published scientific manuscripts that are also described in the GOAT manuscript. Respective PubMed identifiers are included in the dataset names.
